Benin &mdash; Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo State said people raping and killing women in the state are not typical herders as perceived but fleeing Boko Haram terrorists.Two elderly women identified as Christiana and Matina were last week alleged to have been raped and killed at their farms by suspected herders in Ewu community, Esan Central Local Government Area.Speaking during a visit to the families yesterday, Governor Obaseki said the killers were not ordinary herders but Boko Haram fighters who fled from the North-East.He urged security agents to beef up security in the boarder area with Kogi State.